The paper proposes a decision-focused learning approach that integrates a differentiable proxy for common graph optimization problems as a layer in learned systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with optimization problems on graphs, which could place it in the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of clustering and community detection, which could suggest a connection to computer vision (cs.CV).
